public class HasDataFlushableEditor<T>
extends com.google.gwt.editor.client.adapters.ListEditor<T,com.google.gwt.editor.client.ValueAwareEditor<T>>

Extended version of com.google.gwt.editor.client.adapters.HasDataEditor. Able to have data flushed from here, back into the real data Instead of creating FieldUpdater instances that directly modify the data, use a subclass of PendingFieldUpdateChange, with commit() doing the actual changing.
